headlines.description: — A confident De'Aaron Fox stepped the foul line for two shots with 2.4 seconds left and his team trailing by one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings' Fox misses 2 free throws to give Hornets 124-123 win

headlines.description: — Indiana assistant coach Lloyd Pierce walked into Friday night's game uncertain how the Pacers would respond to coach Rick Carlisle's absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers pull away late to beat Mavs 106-93 without Carlisle

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant and James Harden carried the heavy scoring load for the Brooklyn Nets, as usual.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant's 31 points power Nets past Young, Hawks 113-105

events.name: New York Knicks at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 24 points, Fred VanVleet had 17 points and 11 assists, and the Toronto Raptors won their 10th straight home meeting against New York on Friday night, beating the Knicks 90-87.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent Jr. scores 24, Raptors beat struggling Knicks 90-87

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 41 points and 17 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped the Houston Rockets' seven-game winning streak with a 123-114 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Milwaukee ends Houston's 7-game streak with 123-114 win

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen scored 21 points and added 10 rebounds, Darius Garland and Kevin Love also had double-doubles, and the Cleveland Cavaliers used a fast start to cruise 123-106 over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 7 Cavs score in double digits for 123-106 win over Wolves

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 26 points and the New Orleans Pelicans defeated Detroit 109-93 on Friday night, extending the Pistons' losing streak to 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 26, Pelicans extend Pistons' skid to 11 games

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Lakers were ready for the Thunder this time. Having LeBron James on the court was a big reason why.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 33, Lakers roll past Thunder 116-95

headlines.description: — JaVale McGee always brings the energy. On Friday night, he also brought the buckets.
headlines.shortLinkText: McGee scores 21, Suns roll past Celtics 111-90
